title: Fly with von Drake (1963)
description: Take to the skies with "Wings" von Drake's historically accurate (and hysterically funny) lecture on the birth of man-in-flight. Using clever animation and vintage film segments, we begin with flights of fancy (Icarus and his wings of wax, magic carpets, etc.); witness the high-flying inventions of many cultures; glide through the clouds in hot air balloons and airplanes; and finally take the ultimate journey on a rocket ship to the Moon - and beyond!
